Based on your stack and decisions:

**Use [kotlin-logging](https://github.com/oshai/kotlin-logging) + SLF4J/Logback** — it's the standard for Kotlin services and you've already adopted structured logging with correlation IDs.

```kotlin
// build.gradle.kts
dependencies {
    implementation("io.github.oshai:kotlin-logging-jvm:7.0.3")
    implementation("ch.qos.logback:logback-classic:1.5.12")
    implementation("net.logstash.logback:logstash-logback-encoder:8.0") // structured JSON
}
```

```kotlin
import io.github.oshai.kotlinlogging.KotlinLogging

private val logger = KotlinLogging.logger {}

class PaymentProcessor(private val correlationId: String) {

    fun processPayment(paymentId: String, amount: BigDecimal) {
        logger.info { "Processing payment" }  // lazy evaluation

        // structured fields via MDC for correlation IDs
        withLoggingContext("correlationId" to correlationId, "paymentId" to paymentId) {
            logger.info { "Payment initiated amount=$amount" }
            // ...
            logger.warn { "Payment retry triggered" }
        }
    }
}
```

```xml
<!-- logback.xml — JSON output for EKS/CloudWatch -->
<configuration>
  <appender name="STDOUT" class="ch.qos.logback.core.ConsoleAppender">
    <encoder class="net.logstash.logback.encoder.LogstashEncoder">
      <includeMdcKeyName>correlationId</includeMdcKeyName>
      <includeMdcKeyName>paymentId</includeMdcKeyName>
    </encoder>
  </appender>
  <root level="INFO">
    <appender-ref ref="STDOUT" />
  </root>
</configuration>
```

Key points:
- **kotlin-logging** wraps SLF4J with idiomatic Kotlin (lazy messages, extension functions)
- **Logstash encoder** gives you structured JSON — works with your EKS/CloudWatch pipeline
- **MDC** propagates correlation IDs across coroutines (use `MDCContext()` with your coroutine dispatchers)
- Payment services need PCI-aware logging — **never log full card numbers, CVVs, or tokens**

This matches what your other Kotlin services (auth-service, etc.) already use. No new dependencies or infra needed.
